<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-07-30T08:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-07-30T08:24:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Lithuania/26: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-07-30T15:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                        1924—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 3:15
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>118. <hi rend="italic">In re</hi> Lithuanian debt to the United States,
                            Lithuanian Government inquires whether the United States Government
                            would protest the ratification by the Lithuanian Assembly of the trade
                            agreement with Germany which provides for the mutual cancelation of all
                            claims arising out of the war, the German occupation, reparations and
                                <hi rend="italic">post-bellum</hi> supplies, etc. Agreement now
                            before the Assembly. Prompt reply desired.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>